  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is correct. Since it's given that <math alttext=\"upper P\"><mi>P</mi>\n</math> is the center of a circle with a radius of <math alttext=\"9\"><mn>9</mn>\n</math> inches, and that points <math alttext=\"upper Q\"><mi>Q</mi>\n</math> and <math alttext=\"upper R\"><mi>R</mi>\n</math> lie on that circle, it follows that <math alttext=\"line segment upper P upper Q\"><mover><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mo>&macr;</mo></mover></math> and <math alttext=\"line segment upper R upper P\"><mover><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>P</mi></mrow><mo>&macr;</mo></mover></math> of triangle <math alttext=\"upper P upper Q upper R\"><mi>P</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi>R</mi></math> each have a length of <math alttext=\"9\"><mn>9</mn>\n</math> inches. Let the length of <math alttext=\"line segment upper Q upper R\"><mover><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mo>&macr;</mo></mover></math> be <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math> inches. It follows that the perimeter of triangle <math alttext=\"upper P upper Q upper R\"><mi>P</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi>R</mi></math> is <math alttext=\"9 plus 9 plus x\"><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></math> inches. Since it's given that the perimeter of triangle <math alttext=\"upper P upper Q upper R\"><mi>P</mi><mi>Q</mi><mi>R</mi></math> is <math alttext=\"31\"><mn>31</mn>\n</math> inches, it follows that <math alttext=\"9 plus 9 plus x equals 31\"><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>31</mn></math>, or <math alttext=\"18 plus x equals 31\"><mn>18</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>31</mn></math>. Subtracting <math alttext=\"18\"><mn>18</mn>\n</math> from both sides of this equation gives <math alttext=\"x equals 13\"><mrow>\n<mi>x</mi>\n<mo>=</mo>\n<mn>13</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math>. Therefore, the length, in inches, of <math alttext=\"line segment upper Q upper R\"><mover><mrow><mi>Q</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mo>&macr;</mo></mover></math> is <math alttext=\"13\"><mn>13</mn>\n</math>.</